backend

Class OperationManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • backend.BackEnd

  • public class OperationManager
extends java.lang.Object
    This class controls the systems memory elements and performs all the transactions from the DailyTransactions file. It validate each transaction and outputs new UserAccounts and AvailableTickets files for the front end to use the next day.

    • Method Detail

      • processTransactions

        public int processTransactions()
        This method is responsible for looping through the transaction in memory and calling the appropriate method to execute each transaction. It is also responsible for validating input and reporting a fatal error on invalid input.
        Returns:
        0 on success, 1 on failure, 2 on fatal failure.

      • doCreate

        private int doCreate(Regular regular)
        This method executes a create new user transaction on the system. It is called by doTransaction when the transaction code is 01. It proceeds to call the newUser() method in Accounts. If any errors are reported it unit.logs them to xstream.log and outputs the error to terminal.
        Parameters:
        regular - a transaction record of type Regular
        Returns:
        0 on success, 1 on failure.

      • doDelete

        private int doDelete(Regular record)
        This method is responsible for deleting a user account on the system. It is called by doTransaction when the transaction code is 02. It calls the deleteUser method from the Accounts class. If any errors are reported it unit.logs them to xstream.log and terminal.
        Parameters:
        record - a transaction record of type Regular
        Returns:
        0 on success, 1 on failure.

      • doBuy

      • doRefund

        private int doRefund(Return record)
        This method is responsible for performing a refund transaction on the system. It is called by doTransaction when the transaction code is 05. It calls the removeCredit and addCredit method from the Accounts class. Any errors reported are logged in xstream.log and terminal.
        Parameters:
        record - a transaction record of type Refund
        Returns:
        0 on success, 1 on failure.

      • main

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
        xstream - backend This is the main program for running the backend of xstream. To run with specific backend.data files, include the paths in cmd-line. The order is DailyTransactions file, UserAccounts file, AvailableTickets file. If no files are specified then the default backend.data files will be used
        Parameters:
        args - an array of strings from the command-line which represent filenames
